    "title": "BX3 Framework: A Universal Architecture for Intelligent Systems",
    "publication_date": "2026-04-24",
    "description": "We introduce the BX3 Framework, a deterministic, hierarchical architecture for intelligent systems that mandates bounded cognition, enforced physical constraints, and fully forensic logging. BX3 establishes four core layers \u2014 Cognitive, Informational, Physical, and Environmental \u2014 with mandatory human accountability at every tier. This paper presents the formal specification, comparative analysis against existing frameworks, and foundational definitions for all subsequent BX3 papers.",
